The article is a transcript of remarks made by Vice President Mike Pence at a meeting with families of six Americans who are being illegally detained by the Maduro regime in Venezuela. Pence assures the families that the U.S. is with them and will stand with them until their loved ones are free and until Venezuela is free. He condemns the Maduro regime, stating that Nicol√°s Maduro is a dictator with no legitimate claim to power. The families share their stories of their loved ones' detention and express their concerns for their health and safety. Pence calls on the Maduro regime to release the detainees and all political prisoners and emphasizes that democracy and the rule of law must be restored in Venezuela. He also mentions that the U.S. is considering strong action against Cuba for supporting the Venezuelan dictatorship. Pence assures the families that the U.S. will continue to stand firm and bring more pressure on the regime. He mentions that there are a range of economic sanctions that can be imposed on Venezuela and that all options are on the table. Pence concludes by stating that the U.S. will use all means at its disposal to secure the release of the detained Americans.